Use assertions to enforce internal invariants in storage
commitResults.messageBody: Currently, the Storage class checks for unknown task types and malformed task lines using either exceptions or prints. By replacing the default exception and other internal checks with assertions, we document that these conditions should never occur. This improves code safety and maintainability by separating internal invariant checks from external error handling.

commitResults.messageTitle: Delegate command messages to Ui to improve SLAP
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, several command classes directly format and return strings for user output. This violates SLAP.

To improve code clarity and maintainability all commands have been refactored so that messages are delegated to Ui methods. Each command now focuses solely on its core responsibilities, while Ui handles all user-facing output.
